Solution. Let
\[
G(t)=\int_{0}^{t} g(s) d s .
\]

Then \( G^{\prime}=g \). Put \( x=u e^{G}, y=v e^{G} \). Then
\[
\begin{array}{l}
\frac{d x}{d t}=\left(\frac{d u}{d t}+g u\right) e^{G}=h e^{G} \\
\frac{d y}{d t}=\left(\frac{d v}{d t}+g v\right) e^{G} \geq h e^{G}
\end{array}
\]
since \( e^{G}>0 \) for all \( t \). Thus \( (d / d t)(y-x) \geq 0 \). Now \( x(0)=y(0)=c \), and we conclude \( x(t) \leq y(t) \) and therefore \( u(t) \leq v(t) \) for all \( t \geq 0 \).

For the second part of the problem, we suppose that \( v \) satisfies
\[
\frac{d v}{d t}+g v=v^{2} \text { for } t \in\left[0, t_{0}\right], \quad v(0)=c_{1}
\]
and we let \( w \) be any continuous function on \( \left[0, t_{0}\right] \). Then
\[
\begin{array}{c}
(v-w)^{2} \geq 0 \quad \text { for all } t \\
\frac{d v}{d t}+(g-2 w) v=v^{2}-2 w v \geq-w^{2}
\end{array}
\]

If \( W(t)=\int_{0}^{1} w(s) d s \) and \( y=v e^{G 2 w} \) then
\[
\begin{array}{c}
\frac{d y}{d t}=\left(\frac{d v}{d t}+(g-2 w) v\right) e^{G-2 w} \geq-w^{2} e^{G} 2 w \\
y(t) \geq c_{1}-\int_{0}^{\prime} w^{2}(s) \exp [G(s)-2 W(s)] d s \\
v(t) \geq c_{1} \exp [-G(t)+2 W(t)] \\
-\int_{0}^{\prime} \exp [G(s)-G(t)-2(W(s)-W(t))] w^{2}(s) d s
\end{array}
\]

So
\[
\begin{aligned}
v(t) \geq \max _{w}\{ & \left\{c_{1} \exp [-G(t)+2 W(t)]\right. \\
& \left.-\int_{0}^{\prime \prime} \exp [G(s)-G(t)-2(W(s)-W(t))] w^{2}(s) d s\right\}
\end{aligned}
\]

Now if we take \( w=v \), then all of the preceding inequalities become equalities so we conclude
\[
\begin{aligned}
v(t)=\max _{n^{\prime}}\{ & c_{1} \exp [-G(t)+2 W(t)] \\
& \left.-\int_{0}^{t} \exp [G(s)-G(t)-2(W(s)-W(t))] w^{2}(s) d s\right\}
\end{aligned}
\]
which is equivalent to the form given.
The solution of the equation
\[
\frac{d v}{d t}+g v=v^{2}
\]
subject to the initial condition \( v(0)=c_{1} \), may be unbounded on a finite interval, say \( v \rightarrow \infty \) as \( t \mid t_{1} \). Then the preceding analysis is valid only for \( t<t_{1} \). If we pick any \( t_{0} \) with \( 0<t_{0}<t_{1} \), then it is valid for [0, \( \left.t_{0}\right] \).
